        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 6:26PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 626 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Melvern Lake, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Quenemo, Melvern Lake, Olivet, Melvern, and Lyndon.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 156 and 167.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
